<taxonomicName authorityName="STIASSNY &amp; SCHLIEWEN" authorityYear="2007" box="[688,847,1583,1607]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" genus="Congochromis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[688,847,1583,1607]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Congochromis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is diagnosed by the following combination of apomorphic features: four pores in the dentary laterosensory canal (
<figureCitation box="[669,730,1671,1695]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[112,150,1447,1469]" captionTargetBox="[121,1154,211,1412]" captionTargetId="figure-96@3.[121,1154,210,1413]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 1. Isolated infraorbital series, oral jaws, and suspensoria of (A) Congochromis dimidiatus, AMNH" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5388121" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5388121/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">fig. 1</figureCitation>
, *3 
<superScript attach="left" box="[779,789,1666,1682]" fontSize="7" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">1</superScript>
vs. five pores, *3 
<superScript attach="none" box="[1019,1029,1666,1682]" fontSize="7" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">0</superScript>
), absence of a laterosensory canal in the angulo-articular (
<figureCitation box="[669,730,1730,1754]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[112,150,1447,1469]" captionTargetBox="[121,1154,211,1412]" captionTargetId="figure-96@3.[121,1154,210,1413]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 1. Isolated infraorbital series, oral jaws, and suspensoria of (A) Congochromis dimidiatus, AMNH" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5388121" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5388121/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">fig. 1</figureCitation>
, *4 
<superScript attach="left" box="[780,790,1724,1740]" fontSize="7" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">1</superScript>
vs. *4 
<superScript attach="none" box="[882,892,1724,1740]" fontSize="7" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">0</superScript>
), and six pores in the preopercle laterosensory canal (
<figureCitation box="[498,558,1550,1574]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[112,150,1447,1469]" captionTargetBox="[121,1154,211,1412]" captionTargetId="figure-96@3.[121,1154,210,1413]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 1. Isolated infraorbital series, oral jaws, and suspensoria of (A) Congochromis dimidiatus, AMNH" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5388121" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5388121/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">fig. 1</figureCitation>
, *5 
<superScript attach="left" box="[602,612,1544,1560]" fontSize="7" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">1</superScript>
vs. seven pores, *5 
<superScript attach="none" box="[302,312,1574,1590]" fontSize="7" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">0</superScript>
).
</paragraph>
